page.title: 18Wild Flowers In Stickney.
page.content: In Stickney there is a Picnic Area,and there are alot of trees,grass,wild flowers and animals.The Picnic Area once had a railway running through it, with a meadow by its side.On the other side of the road there was the railway station, where there was another meadow.This has now been dug up,and sold for farm land.We visited the Picnic Area to see what we could find. We concentrated on wild flowers.These are some that we found. Dog Rose, Yarrow, Black Medic, Correl Grass, Cudweed, Goats Beard, Horse Tail, Pineapple Weed, Oat Grass, Common Spotted Orchid, Good Friday Grass, Green Veined Orchid, Our favourite weed was the Pineapple Weed,because when you squeezed it ever so hard you got a smell of Pineapple.
